You said:
a of frontend engineer line should be small or capital letter
2/2
ChatGPT said:

Use small letter a a Frontend Engineer

Correct

Hi! I'm Shubham, a Frontend Engineer

Not correct

Hi! I'm Shubham, A Frontend Engineer

Why a should be lowercase

1. Grammar rule

The article a is never capitalized in the middle of a sentence (unless it starts the sentence).

2. Visual hierarchy

Lowercase a keeps the focus on Frontend Engineer, not on the article.

3. Professional standard

Most portfolios follow this pattern:

  • a Software Engineer

  • a Product Designer

  • a Frontend Developer

Using capital A looks incorrect and visually awkward.

Final Version (Correct & Professional)

Hi! I'm Shubham, a Frontend Engineer

If you want, I can also check spacing, alignment, and styling for perfect typography.
